## Image Handling

### Pre-Attach Optimization

Before attaching screenshots or images:

```bash
# Resize to max dimensions
magick input.png -resize 2000x2000\> output.png

# Compress JPEG
magick input.jpg -resize 2000x2000\> -quality 85 output.jpg

# Convert format if needed
magick input.bmp -resize 2000x2000\> output.png
```

### Format Guidelines

| Content | Format | Quality |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Text/UI | PNG | Lossless |
| Photos | JPEG | 85% |
| Diagrams | PNG | Lossless |
| Screenshots | PNG | Default |

---

## PDF Handling

### Size Guidelines

| Size | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| < 3MB | Inlined as document |
| 3-20MB | Extracted to page images |
| > 20MB | Reference only |
| > 100 pages | Reference only |

### Partial Reading

```
# Read specific pages
Read document.pdf {"pages": "1-10"}
Read document.pdf {"pages": "15,20,25"}
```

### Pre-Conversion

```bash
# Convert to text
pdftotext -layout document.pdf document.txt

# Or to Markdown
markitdown document.pdf > document.md
```

---

## MCP Server Management

### Disable Unused Servers

Each MCP server adds to system prompt size:

```
# List active
/mcp list

# Disable unused
/mcp disable <server-name>
```

### Official vs Custom

- **Official registry MCPs**: Tool names logged (not PII)
- **Custom/local MCPs**: Tool names redacted to `mcp_tool`

---

## Rate Limit Management

### Monitor Headers

The API sends these headers (tracked automatically):
- `anthropic-ratelimit-unified-5h-*` - 5-hour session limits
- `anthropic-ratelimit-unified-7d-*` - 7-day weekly limits
- `anthropic-ratelimit-unified-overage-*` - Extra usage status

### Early Warnings

- **5-hour**: Warning at 90% utilization
- **7-day**: Tiered warnings at 25%, 50%, 75%

### Overage

When main limit hits, overage quota activates (if enabled in account settings).

---

## Summary Checklist

### Before Starting Work

- [ ] Set appropriate model (Haiku/Sonnet/Opus)
- [ ] Enable auto-compact in settings
- [ ] Verify MCP servers (disable unused)
- [ ] Pre-convert any binary documents

### During Session

- [ ] Use offset/limit for file reads
- [ ] Set token budgets (+500k) for large tasks
- [ ] Run `/compact` at 150K tokens
- [ ] Avoid model switching

### For Large Projects

- [ ] Use plan mode (`/plan`) for complex tasks
- [ ] Batch operations by file type
- [ ] Pre-resize images before attaching
- [ ] Convert PDFs to text when possible

---

## Emergency Controls

### Hard Token Limits

```bash
# Set absolute limit (blocks if exceeded)
export CLAUDE_CODE_BLOCKING_LIMIT_OVERRIDE=180000
```

### Disable Expensive Features

```bash
# Disable advisor tool
export CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_ADVISOR_TOOL=1

# Disable attachments
export CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_ATTACHMENTS=1

# Disable background tasks
export CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_BACKGROUND_TASKS=1
```

### Privacy Mode

```bash
# Disable all telemetry
export DISABLE_TELEMETRY=1

# Disable nonessential traffic
export CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC=1
```

